The Lagos State government has said that despite the end of the Eid celebrations, the sale of its popular rice brand, Lake Rice, will continue at all designated centres across the state. The Permanent Secretary, Ministry of Agriculture, Dr Olayiwole Onasanya, affirmed that bags of the product would be available at various centres across the state. The centres include the Agricultural Development Authority Complex, Oko-Oba; Lagos State Agriculture Inputs Supply Authority (LAISA), Ojo, and the Blue Roof at LTV Complex, Agidingbi, Ikeja; Teslim Balogun Stadium, Surulere; Ministry of Agriculture Area Office, Ajah, and the Mobolaji Johnson Sports Centre, Rowe Park, Yaba. He restated that the price of a 50kg bag of the Lake Rice would still be sold for N14,000 and the 25kg bag forÂ  N7,000, while the 10kg bag would go for N3,000. Sallah: Lagos floods market with 700 trailer loads of rice Lagos Govt confirms delay in sales of Lake Rice Eid el-Kabir celebration: Lagos begins sale of Lake Rice Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin